replies.body:
I find that with his insane clear speed I can clear one side of jungle and then gank a lane, then grabbing the coresponding rift scuttler and herald/drag. This gets me fed on the enemy laner, creates insane pressure on the side of the map, and then from there I can shift mid, gank and clear the other half, doing the same as before.

Edit: Read that so fucking wrong. I thought you were saying "Get sated and don't fuckin do nothin.
{{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}

I'm both guilty and not guilty.

I usually play Sated Devour junglers (because I'm a scumbag). {{champion:11}} 

I try to make a goal to clear ASAP, but I'm always peeking at lanes.

Whereas, I sort of agree with OP on his/her stance.

I agree with you as well. Sometimes, I honestly forget to gank a lane, or will back off if you're pushed up. I'm not selfish, I try my best. I've gone roughly 8-4-5 while trying to get sated, but still lose due to their team being overall better (or cheese). Stuff happens, regardless of ganks. Trying to assist your laners, rather than farming all game helps your team. Now, if **every**, or at least more junglers would get this mentality, games would be nicer.

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
